<div class="sh-hero">
  <div>
    <h1>Get <span class="sh-accent">Hired</span></h1>
    <p>
      A job-application portal built to make the Durham College hiring experience more user-friendly and efficient.
      Users sign up with their details securely stored and passwords hashed, then log in to build a profile, upload
      a resume, apply for open positions, and track which jobs they have applied to. It was built with Eleventy and
      Nunjucks on the front end and a Node/Express back end backed by MongoDB.
    </p>
    <div class="sh-tech">
      <span>JavaScript</span><span>Node.js</span><span>Express</span><span>MongoDB</span>
      <span>Eleventy (11ty)</span><span>Nunjucks</span><span>Bootstrap</span><span>HTML · CSS</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <figure class="sh-herofig m-0">
    <img src="/src/image/jobs_page.png" data-zoom alt="Get Hired job listings page">
  </figure>
</div>

